<p>Supplementary information from Sergey Lebedev:  All instrumental
music was composed in medieval style by Elizabeth Gaver; polyphonic
arrangements are by Barbara Thornton.  The &quot;Interlude&quot;
is not a part of Hildegard's original play, but rather some other
material (from <i>Symphoniae harmoniae revelationum caelestium</i>)
the performers have added from the same manuscript.</p>

